<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ920122-0075</DOCNO><DOCID>920122-0075.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Kroger Co.:   Charge of $11.7 Million Set   To Be Taken in 4th Period</HL><DATE>01/22/92</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B3</SO><CO>   KR</CO><MS>CONSUMER NON-CYCLICAL (NCY)</MS><IN>FOOD RETAILERS AND WHOLESALERS, CONVENIENCE STORES (FDR)</IN><NS>FINANCING AGREEMENTS (FNC)</NS><RE>NORTH AMERICA (NME)OHIO (OH)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   Kroger Co. said it will report a charge of $11.7 millionin the fourth quarter because of the early retirement ofdebt.   The Cincinnati supermarket chain also said preliminaryfourth-quarter results show sales increased 2.9% andoperating cash flow fell 5% to 7%, compared with year-agofigures. In the year-ago quarter, Kroger earned $66.9million, or 77 cents a share, on sales of $4.99 billion.</LP><TEXT>   Separately, Kroger said it signed a credit agreement thatextends the maturity on its senior bank debt by two years andpermits the company to borrow an additional $500 million ofsenior secured financing under certain conditions.</TEXT></DOC>